### =============================================================================
### Exercise 5 — Sandbox Extensibility
###
### Exercises the validateReview extension point wired into submitForReview.
### Two paths are covered — pick the one matching your setup:
###
###   Path A — standalone iteration on the extension template (port 4006)
###     Prereq: `cd xstravels-ext && npm install && cds watch`
###     Fastest edit-save-test loop; no mtx sidecar needed.
###
###   Path B — production-like tenant push (port 4004)
###     Prereq: xstravels has multitenancy + sandbox enabled;
###             sidecar on 4005; main app on 4004 with --with-mtx;
###             tenant t1 subscribed  (cds subscribe t1 --to http://localhost:4005 -u yves:);
###             extension pushed      (cds push --to http://localhost:4005 -u bob:).
###
### The requests below fire against the app itself and run as `alice` (admin).
### Only the sidecar CLI calls (subscribe/push/pull) need the other users.
###
### The requests are identical between paths — only the base URL changes.
###
### Reading responses:
###   204 No Content → success. submitForReview / reopenTravel return no body
###     on success; this is the expected outcome, NOT an error. Re-read the
###     travel with the follow-up GET to confirm the Status_code flipped.
###   409 Conflict → either the framework's `@from` guard (INVALID_FLOW_...)
###     or the extension handler's `req.reject(409, "...")`. Both look the
###     same to the client, by design.
### =============================================================================

@app  = http://localhost:4006
### Switch to @app = http://localhost:4004 for Path B (tenant push).

@service = {{app}}/odata/v4/travel
@auth    = Basic alice:


### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Helpers — find suitable travels for the three policy scenarios
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### List a couple of Open travels with low TotalPrice — pass all rules
GET {{service}}/Travels?$top=3&$select=ID,Status_code,TotalPrice,Currency_code&$filter=Status_code eq 'O' and TotalPrice lt 1000
Authorization: {{auth}}

### List a couple of Open USD travels with high TotalPrice — trip Rule 1 (total cap)
GET {{service}}/Travels?$top=3&$select=ID,Status_code,TotalPrice,Currency_code&$filter=Status_code eq 'O' and Currency_code eq 'USD' and TotalPrice gt 10000
Authorization: {{auth}}

### Find travels that carry a single Booking above 5000 — trip Rule 2b (per-booking cap)
GET {{service}}/Bookings?$top=5&$select=Travel_ID,Pos,FlightPrice&$filter=FlightPrice gt 5000
Authorization: {{auth}}


### =============================================================================
### 5.1 — Total-price cap (10 000)
###   With the handler enabled (Step 5.1 of the exercise):
###     if travel.TotalPrice > 10000 → req.reject(409, "Total price ...")
### =============================================================================

### ✅ Cheap travel → succeeds, Status_code flips to 'P' (InReview)
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=13,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.submitForReview
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Confirm the transition
GET {{service}}/Travels?$filter=ID eq 13&$select=ID,Status_code,TotalPrice,Currency_code
Authorization: {{auth}}

### ❌ Expensive travel → 409, "Total price 12405 exceeds the 10000 policy limit"
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=6,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.submitForReview
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}


### =============================================================================
### 5.3 — Empty-bookings + per-booking cap (5 000)
###   With the handler extended (Step 5.3):
###     if !bookings.length → "Travel has no bookings ..."
###     if bookings.some(b => b.FlightPrice > 5000) → "At least one booking ..."
### =============================================================================

### Prep: Travel 660 is seeded as Rejected in USD, and its single booking sits at 6053.
### Reopen it first so it becomes Open and eligible for submitForReview.
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=660,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.reopenTravel
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### ❌ Per-booking cap → 409, "At least one booking exceeds the 5000 per-booking cap"
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=660,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.submitForReview
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### For the empty-bookings rule, create a fresh travel with no bookings, then
### activate the draft, then submit for review.
###
### If your setup keeps the draft after CREATE, replace <NEW_ID> below with the
### ID returned from this POST.
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description":   "Empty trip",
  "BeginDate":     "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":       "2026-08-15",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":     "070001",
  "Customer_ID":   "000001"
}

### Activate the draft (replace <NEW_ID>)
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=<NEW_ID>,IsActiveEntity=false)/TravelService.draftActivate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### ❌ Empty travel → 409, "Travel has no bookings — cannot submit for review"
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=<NEW_ID>,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.submitForReview
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}


### =============================================================================
### 5.6 — Currency-aware limits (bonus)
###   With the CurrencyLimits table added:
###     USD MaxTravel = 10000     SGD MaxTravel = 14000
###     USD MaxBooking = 5000     SGD MaxBooking = 7000
### =============================================================================

### ✅ SGD travel, Total ~10 927 → passes (SGD MaxTravel is 14 000, would fail under USD's 10 000 cap)
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=533,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.submitForReview
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Confirm SGD travel is now InReview
GET {{service}}/Travels?$filter=ID eq 533&$select=ID,Status_code,TotalPrice,Currency_code
Authorization: {{auth}}
